@salvadord That's a perfectly fine way to choose form a set of cell instances where some subset may or may not have some properties, but the specification of which cell parameter set to use for a specific population is different: there has to be one and only one cell/cellParam that is used for the population. This suggests the best way to identify this is with the id in:

     netParams.addCellParams('IT', cellRule)   # the "cellParam id"

because there can only ever be one of these. The approach of "try to find one of the cells based on this set of conditions" is a bit loose when it comes to specifying which cell is in a population. Also, there's nothing to stop a user adding multiple cells with identical cellType & cellModel values but different cellParam ids... In that case which one will be used in the population is not specified...

